726072f-a.text:
(1)
Astoria Boulevard, east from 32nd Street. Most of the buildings seen in this view--they being on the north side of the thoroughfare--were raed in 19344 when the Queens approach to the Triborough Bridge was constructed here.
P. L. Sperr  March 11, 1931
(2)
Astoria Boulevard, at 33rd Street, showing, at a later date, the buildings seen in the immediate foreground in view 1 being demolished. The view is northwestward toward 31st Street, where the I.R.T. 'El' station is visible.
P. L. Sperr  September 20, 1934
The N.E. corner of Astoria Boulevard and 32nd Street
P.L.Sperr  September 20, 1934
